    "test_strategy": {
      "evidence": [
        "README.md defines contract-governance expectations and references `goseg/protocol/contracts/contracts_test.go` plus a path-aware CI gate, but the reviewed contract source files (`protocol_contracts.go`, `startram_contracts.go`) only declare catalog data and snapshot helpers with no local invariant hooks (e.g., uniqueness/lifecycle assertions) that would fail fast when entries drift.",
        "goseg/system/metrics/metrics.go reads live host paths (`/proc/mounts`, `/dev/disk/by-label`, `/sys/class/hwmon`) and uses real timing (`cpu.Percent(time.Second, false)`), but README quality gates list generic `go test ./...` plus selected integration packages and do not document a dedicated strategy for deterministic metrics validation across host/runtime variability."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "medium"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "test_strategy",
      "identifier": "contract_catalog_drift_not_guarded_locally",
      "summary": "Contract compatibility metadata changes rely on process policy instead of local executable invariants, making regression detection fragile.",
      "related_files": [
        "README.md",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "README.md requires per-contract lifecycle assertions in `goseg/protocol/contracts/contracts_test.go` and CI gating for contract-surface changes.",
        "protocol_contracts.go and startram_contracts.go define mutable catalog specs/snapshots and compatibility metadata, but include no local self-checking mechanism in the reviewed files to enforce uniqueness/lifecycle consistency at definition time.",
        "Because governance is externalized to workflow, metadata drift (e.g., contract ID/version/compatibility inconsistency) is only caught if external tests remain fully synchronized with these files."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Add table-driven contract invariant tests tightly coupled to each catalog file (or shared invariant helpers called from per-file tests) that assert ID uniqueness, namespace/action consistency, non-empty IntroducedIn/Compatibility, and snapshot immutability behavior; keep CI gate as secondary protection rather than primary detection.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "policy_not_embedded_as_executable_checks"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "test_strategy",
      "identifier": "metrics_runtime_coupling_lacks_documented_test_plan",
      "summary": "Metrics collection is tightly coupled to host runtime state without a documented deterministic test strategy, increasing flake and blind-spot risk.",
      "related_files": [
        "README.md",
        "goseg/system/metrics/metrics.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "metrics.go reads live OS/hardware endpoints (`/proc/mounts`, `/dev/disk/by-label`, `/sys/class/hwmon`) and waits real time for CPU usage (`time.Second` sampling).",
        "README backend quality gate does not specify targeted metrics package strategy or matrix conditions for these host-coupled paths.",
        "Current implementation has no injected seams for filesystem/time dependencies in the reviewed file, so deterministic unit validation of failure/edge paths is difficult."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce dependency seams for filesystem reads, statfs, and CPU sampler/time source, then add deterministic unit tests for mount parsing, label decoding, scanner/statfs error paths, and temperature-source absence; document required host/integration coverage for metrics in README quality gate.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "policy_not_embedded_as_executable_checks"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Quality controls are primarily documented as process/CI policy rather than enforced by close-to-code deterministic tests around volatile contract/runtime boundaries.",
      "Host-dependent runtime code lacks test seams, so strategic risk areas are harder to validate with stable automated tests."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "contract_catalog_drift_not_guarded_locally",
      "metrics_runtime_coupling_lacks_documented_test_plan"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
  }
